column2: Scattered clouds- small ripples- debris in water
Sunny- windy- choppy- no white caps
Water calm - heavy waves (not whitecaps) - hazy sky.
Wind calm- bottom 24.75'- much algae within water.
Sunny- slight ripple- lots of Mayfly hatched this year-fishing bad!  Any connection   No fish
Algae-small spheres concentrated in upper 1 cm. in water.
Prairie du sac dam- temp. 1' 78 degrees- 30' 70 degrees.
Bright day- algal bloom- and calm.
Moon Valley River.  Temperature at 1' is 79 degrees and at 22' the temperature is 76 degrees.
Lots of debris.  Slight ripple stirred up algae-highest water level we've seen since '79.  High level cleaned out marshes
Moon valley.  Temp (1') =68 degrees- temp (20') =68 degrees.
Temp. 1'=64.5- temp. 38'=62. No algae visible. PDS dam.
Sunny- very choppy (no whitecaps) . Daily blue heron sightings!
Algae rods in water. temp 1'=78. temp. 35'-75.
Clarity reduced by algae- also phosphate and chlorophyll
Much less algae and deeper secchi readings than elsewhere on the lake.  Band of compacted algae on surface along downwind of shoreline.
Green/brown in color.  Slight ripple- after bit storm stirred up lake and added sediment particles.
Custer=8- sunny- 70  deg. F- wind northeast 10 mph.
Sunny- 80  deg. F- wind 20 mph- partly cloudy- hazy.

Mostly sunny- the temperature is 86 degrees- southwest wind at 10-15 mph- and color cluster is 3.
Sunny- the temperature is 70 degrees- and westerly wind at 5mph.
Partly cloudy- the temperature is 58 degrees- easterly wind at 5 mph- and the color cluster is 5.
Partly cloudy- the temperature is 55 degrees- southwest wind at 20 mph- and the color cluster is 8.
Lake water is Brown with Nickel Size patches of Green Patches of Algae
I was out sick so this is my first test when coming back. Lake looks good.
blue green intermingled with brown - clear
Rough weather - 4 ft waves Temp unit drifts after 12 ft depth
Big storms north of site earlier in the week.
